      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIVERINA FLASH (1) was restrained from a wide gate on the front line last start and couldn't come on, finishing 7 metres from the winner in sixth at Bathurst over 1730m. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Won't find this any harder and he can finish a lot closer this time. ROCKET ME (8) was successful at his most recent outing by a neck at Young over 2100m after an encouraging minor placing the start before. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row. Has the class to take this out. MAGIC MATTEO (10) is right in contention after finishing in the placings for the second time in a row last start, beaten 5.5 metres into second at Riverina Paceway. No reason he cannot take this out. GET UP BETTY (4) must be included after winning her past two starts, the latest at this track a week ago.",
